programme.title: Gogglebox
programme.desc: The amateur critics share their opinions on what they have been watching during the week as this popular series returns for its ninth run. For some of the contributors the programme has offered a springboard to media success in their own right - I'm a Celebrity winner Scarlett Moffatt being the prime example. Craig Cash narrates.(n)

Kate Armstrong (Jones) is the master chef who is equally intense both in and out of the kitchen. Though Kate's "Type A" personality serves her well when whipping up meals in the trendy Manhattan eatery where she has made a name for herself, it threatens to sink her when she is named as the guardian of her nine-year-old niece Zoe (Little Miss Sunshine's Abigail Breslin). Yet, despite the fact that they couldn't be more different on the surface, there's no denying the strong attraction between Kate and Nick. Arthur is a high-school student from a dysfunctional family, and does everything in his power to avoid hanging around the house while mom and dad quarrel. When he's not practicing his trombone and performing with the high-school marching band, Arthur can usually be found bussing tables at the local Chinese restaurant and flirting with older waitress Annie. Annie used to be Arthur's babysitter, and is currently struggling to separate from her former high-school sweetheart, Glenn. But being a single mother isn't easy, especially since the troubled Glenn wants nothing more than to clean up his act and reunite his family. Back at school, Arthur and pretty classmate Lila (Olivia Thirlby) have been bonding over their mutual love for all things geeky. Though the casual friendship shows promise of evolving into something more when Lila expresses her true feelings for Arthur, he can't help but becoming distracted by his chaotic family life: his father is moving out of the family home, and his mother is doing everything in her power to maintain some semblance of normalcy. programme.title: The Hunger Games
programme.desc: Jennifer Lawrence stars in Gary Ross's Bafta Award-winning action-thriller adaptation of Suzanne Collins' best-selling novel. The dystopian nation of Panem has emerged from the post-apocalyptic remains of the USA. It's a land governed mercilessly from its wealthy central metropolis, the Capitol: following a series of quashed revolts, it demands an annual tribute from each of its 12 outlying regions of a boy and a girl between the ages of 12 and 18. The youngsters, in a warped method of simultaneously controlling and entertaining Panem's populace, are sentenced to hunt each other in televised lethal combat in an area of enclosed woodland; the last person alive is the winner. Sixteen-year-old Katniss Everdeen (Lawrence) is part of the latest contest, having voluntarily taken the place of her younger sister. In addition to her compassion, her resourcefulness, steely determination and collaborative instinct could tip the balance in her favour. But the fight to the death is complicated (for protagonists, viewers and organisers alike) when fellow competitor Peeta Mellark (Josh Hutcherson) professes his love for her. However, the film, which touches on themes of wealth inequality, the power of TV and exposure to violence, belongs to Lawrence, whose portrayal of a strong, believable central female character is devoid of the usual sexist fripperies and has drawn widespread critical acclaim. Also starring Woody Harrelson, Stanley Tucci and Elizabeth Banks. While the violence within the movie is largely implied, some younger viewers could still find the tenor of the film disturbing(n)

programme.title: Goodfellas
programme.desc: Martin Scorsese directs this hard-hitting, highly-acclaimed contemporary gangster drama, based on the memoirs of a real-life Mafia 'wise guy'. Set on the streets of New York, the film follows the rise through the ranks of organised crime of Henry Hill, a small-time hustler who enters the sprawling crime organisation as a runner for neighbourhood don Paul Sorvino. Moving through the mob milieu, Hill comes into contact with veteran Irish hood Robert De Niro, who takes the youngster under his wing to teach him the unwritten rules of the underworld and impress upon him the value of loyalty to the members of his surrogate 'family'(n)

programme.title: The Departed
programme.desc: Legendary director Martin Scorsese takes the helm for this tale of questionable loyalties and blurring identities set in the South Boston organized crime scene and inspired by the wildly popular 2002 Hong Kong crime film Infernal Affairs. As the police force attempts to reign in the increasingly powerful Irish mafia, authorities are faced with the prospect of sending in an undercover agent or seeing their already frail grip on the criminal underworld slip even further. Billy Costigan (Leonardo DiCaprio) is a young cop looking to make a name for himself in the world of law enforcement. Collin Sullivan (Matt Damon) is a street-smart criminal who has successfully infiltrated the police department with the sole intention of reporting their every move to ruthless syndicate head Frank Costello (Jack Nicholson). When Costigan is assigned the task of working his way into Costello's tightly guarded inner circle, Sullivan is faced with the responsibility of rooting out the informer before things get out of hand. With the stakes constantly rising and time quickly running out for the undercover cop and his criminal counterpart, each man must work feverishly to reveal his counterpart before his identity is exposed by the other. Martin Sheen, Alec Baldwin, and Ray Winstone co-star, and writer William Monahan adapts a screenplay originally penned by Alan Mak and Felix Chong(n)

programme.title: Titanic
programme.desc: James Cameron's Oscar-laden epic tells of the first and final voyage of the 'unsinkable' luxury liner through the love story of two very different passengers. Leonardo DiCaprio plays Jack Dawson, a brash chancer in the steerage part of the ship who talks his way up to the staterooms and fancy restaurants where he meets Rose DeWitt Bukater. She is promised to Cal Hockley in a loveless match but falls for Jack. The first half of the film establishes their story, the second the fate of the Titanic once it has struck the iceberg. The destinies of all the crew and passengers are mirrored by the tragedy that befalls the two lovers, while spectacular special effects recreate the ship's fate(n)

programme.title: Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix
programme.desc: Young wizard-in-training Harry Potter (Daniel Radcliffe) returns to Hogwarts for his fifth year of studies, only to find that the magical community seems to be in a curious state of denial about his recent encounter with the sinister Lord Voldemort (Ralph Fiennes) in the fifth installment of the popular fantasy film series based on the best-selling books by author J.K. Rowling. Rumor has it that the dreaded Lord Voldemort has returned, but Minister for Magic Cornelius Fudge (Robert Hardy) isn't so sure what to make of all the hearsay currently floating around the campus of Hogwarts. Suspecting that Headmaster Albus Dumbledore (Michael Gambon) may be fueling the rumors regarding Voldemort's return in order to undermine his authority and lay claim to his job, Fudge entrusts newly arrived Defense Against the Dark Arts professor Dolores Umbridge (Imelda Staunton) with the task of tracking Dumbledore and keeping a protective watch over the nervous student body. The young wizards of Hogwarts will need something much more effective than Umbridge's Ministry-approved course in defensive magic if they are to truly succeed in the extraordinary battle that lies ahead, however, and when the administration fails to provide the students with the tools that they will need to defend Hogwarts against the fearsome powers of the Dark Arts, Hermione (Emma Watson), Ron (Rupert Grint), and Harry take it upon themselves to recruit a small group of students to form "Dumbledore's Army" in preparation for the ultimate supernatural showdown(n)

programme.title: Be Kind Rewind
programme.desc: After a freak accident causes all the tapes in a video store to be erased, an employee and his pal decide to make their own no-budget re-creations of various movies. Jack Black and Mos Def star in this sweet and surreal fable from director Michel Gondry ("The Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind"). Danny Glover, Mia Farrow, Melonie Diaz, Sigourney Weaver(n)

programme.title: The Wrestler

programme.title: Reindeer Games
programme.desc: Just released from prison, all Rudy Duncan wants is to start a new life with Ashley, the girl of his dreams, whom he met through pen-pal letters in prison. But between them and happiness stands her crazy brother, Gabriel, and his motley crew of deadly criminals who think Rudy has some inside information about a casino where he once had a job(n)

programme.title: The Maze Runner: The Scorch Trials
programme.desc: In the next installment of the "Maze Runner" franchise Thomas (Dylan O'Brien), Teresa (Kaya Scodelario) and the rest of the Gladers search for clues about WCKD, a powerful organization in the Scorch, a bleak landscape that is filled with dangerous obstacles. The Gladers partner with resistance fighters to take on WCKD in an attempt to discover their plans for the future in this young-adult dystopian thriller from 20th Century Fox. Directed by Wes Ball who previously directed the original film, The Maze Runner. Cast includes Thomas Brodie-Sangster, Giancarlo Esposito, Aidan Gillen, Ki Hong Lee, Barry Pepper, Lili Taylor and Patricia Clarkson(n)

programme.title: Phone Booth
programme.desc: A dangerous sniper traps a publicist in a public phone booth(n)

programme.title: Resident Evil
programme.desc: Alice leads a team of commandos into the multi-national Umbrella Corporation's locked-down bunker, which is controlled by the main computer, The Red Queen. The unit is sealed because of a virus that gassed all the staff but, as Alice and her team discover, the virus has re-animated them. Now, as well as facing the computer's weaponry, they must tackle the living dead to prevent the virus escaping into the outside world. Paul W Anderson's horror thriller is based on the successful computer game(n)

programme.title: San Andreas
programme.desc: In this high-octane thriller, the infamous San Andreas Fault gives way, producing a devastating earthquake across California. A highly skilled helicopter pilot (Dwayne Johnson) races to save his ex-wife (Carla Gugino) in Los Angeles before the complete destruction of the city. After one daring rescue, the pilot flies north toward San Francisco in search of his estranged daughter (Alexandra Daddario), racing against time and the inevitable aftershocks that promise to devastate the coastline(n)

programme.title: American Gangster
programme.desc: Set in the early 1970s, this biopic stars Denzel Washington as real-life New York City drug kingpin Frank Lucas, and Russell Crowe as the cop sworn to bring him down(n)

programme.title: The Strangers
programme.desc: Scott Speedman and Liv Tyler star in this nail-biting suspense thriller about a young couple who are terrorized by three masked intruders at a secluded country house. Gemma Ward, Kip Weeks, Laura Margolis, Glenn Howerton. Written and directed by Bryan Bertino(n)

programme.desc: An authority on rare books is drawn into a confrontation with the forces of darkness in this thriller directed by Roman Polanski. Dean Corso (Johnny Depp) is a rare book broker who makes his living tracking down valuable items for rich bibliophiles. Corso is hired by Boris Balkan (Frank Langella), a millionaire New Yorker with a vast collection of occult literature and a keen interest in "The Nine Gates to the Kingdom of Shadows." Legend has it that the book was co-written by Satan in the 17th century, and only three copies are known to exist; the owner of one recently sold the book to Balkan a few days before killing himself. Balkan wants Corso to find the other two copies (one owned by a Mr. Fargas in Portugal and the other by a French collector named Kessler) and examine them to determine if they are forgeries. Corso is told to be thorough and spare no expense. He begins by visiting Liana Telfer (Lena Olin), the widow of the man who once owned Balkan's copy of the book, who has an unusually strong desire to get the book back, and confers with his friend Bernie (James Russo), who soon turns up dead, in a manner much like an illustration from the book. programme.desc: Coverage from Chepstow, Lingfield Park, Newcastle, Wolverhampton, Fairyhouse and Meydan.(n)

programme.title: Stateside
programme.desc: Live coverage from the United States.(n)

programme.title: Breakfast
programme.desc: Round-up of national and international news, plus the latest from the money markets.(n)

programme.title: Britain's Home Truths
programme.desc: Nicki Chapman looks at the development of new towns across the UK, meeting the planners who created them and the residents who turned them into homes. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Homes Under the Hammer
programme.desc: Lucy Alexander and Martin Roberts explore a house with no floor in Edgbaston, Birmingham, a detached house in Oldham, Greater Manchester, and a former garage complex ripe for development in Forest Hill in south London as the three properties come up for auction.(n)

programme.title: Wanted Down Under Revisited
programme.desc: Four years after a trial week spent in New Zealand, Nicki Chapman catches up with the Fitzpatrick family, to find out if prison officer Billy managed to convince reluctant wife Beth to take the plunge and move to Auckland on a permanent basis.(n)

programme.title: Oxford Street Revealed
programme.desc: A policeman has a shift to remember as he takes on dangerous cars, drunks and rooftop intruders, and the secret world of bicycle couriers is examined. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Bargain Hunt
programme.desc: Two teams race around an antiques fair at the Oswestry Showground in Shropshire. Anita Manning presents, while experts John Cameron and Thomas Plant offer advice.(n)

programme.title: Doctors
programme.sub-title: The Best Days of Your Life.
programme.desc: Heston attempts to avoid an old enemy, while Mrs Tembe enlists JJ's help to try to understand the poor food being served at the hospital.(n)

programme.title: The Coroner
programme.desc: A member of a small group of treasure hunters dies shortly after finding some gold coins with his metal detector. Davey thinks he died of natural causes but Jane isn't so sure. Professor Tal Greening confirms the coins are fakes, and it soon transpires the deceased has been poisoned. Crime drama guest starring Katy Brand, with Claire Goose and Matt Bardock.(n)

programme.title: Escape to the Country
programme.desc: Jonnie Irwin helps a pair of music lovers who want to relocate to a more rural area, as they plan to leave their urban lifestyles behind for the Cambridgeshire countryside, on a budget of £500,000. Meanwhile, away from the property hunt, Jonnie visits one of the largest Bronze Age sites in Britain.(n)

programme.title: The Farmers' Country Showdown
programme.desc: Two farmers with cutting-edge ideas compete against each other in the Cream Awards. Cornwall duo Hayden and Jack both hope to secure the young farmer of the year title.(n)

programme.title: Flog It
programme.desc: Antiques experts Charles Hanson and Adam Partridge unearth all manner of items to auction in Morecambe, Lancashire, including French porcelain and Japanese carvings.(n)

programme.title: Pointless
programme.desc: Quiz show in which pairs of contestants try to score the fewest points possible by giving the least obvious correct answers to questions posed to 100 people before the show. At the end of each round, the team with the most points is eliminated until the final two pairs battle for the chance to compete for a cash prize. Presented by Alexander Armstrong and Richard Osman.(n)

programme.title: The One Show
programme.desc: Angela Scanlon hosts the final edition of the week, featuring the usual mix of celebrity guests and stories about people in extraordinary circumstances.(n)

programme.title: A Question of Sport
programme.desc: European 800m champion Lynsey Sharp, golfer Andrew Johnston, South Africa rugby union star JP Pietersen and former Bolton Wanderers striker Kevin Davies join regular team captains Matt Dawson and Phil Tufnell and host Sue Barker on the light-hearted quiz.(n)

programme.title: EastEnders
programme.desc: Konrad invites Shirley out for dinner and after Mick receives disappointing news about the Vic ceiling, the local shopkeeper offers to fix it for half the price. Denise speaks to a journalist about the state of the community, while Ian suffers an embarrassing incident, prompting him to tell Jane the truth about what the nurse said to him.(n)

programme.title: Room 101
programme.desc: Frank Skinner invites sports presenter Gabby Logan and comedians Richard Ayoade and Alun Cochrane to express their anger over people, events and objects that upset them, as the trio vie to banish their top peeves, annoyances, irritation or worst nightmares consigned to oblivion. Their gripes include people who laugh out loud when reading a book, half-and-half scarves - and fun.(n)

programme.title: Not Going Out
programme.desc: Lee and Lucy decide to attend a marriage counselling session. However, events soon put their relationship under further strain. Comedy, starring Lee Mack and Sally Bretton.(n)

programme.title: Tracey Ullman's Show
programme.desc: Songstress Adele is happy - but that's not helping her new album. A hard working mother tries to juggle her work life balance, while this week's vlog from Dame Maggie has some of the best acting tips imaginable. Meanwhile, a therapist has trouble with confidentiality and politician Nicola Sturgeon is in her lair with a song about her plans for world domination. Another selection of inventive comedy sketches, with Ben Miller as media mogul Rupert Murdoch and featuring a guest appearance by Nigel Havers.(n)

programme.title: The Graham Norton Show
programme.desc: Among Graham's guests are Hugh Jackman, who is about to make his final appearance as a world-weary Wolverine in the X-Men sequel Logan, alongside co-star Patrick Stewart, aka Professor X, who also takes a seat on the sofa. Plus, the host subjects more audience members to the dreaded red chair - so their stories had better be good.(n)

programme.title: The Real Marigold Hotel
programme.desc: The celebrities continue to settle into life in their 16th-century mansion, and are brought closer together when they celebrate Amanda Barrie's 81st birthday together. Lionel Blair - who has struggled with a distended belly since having treatment for cancer - tries out a local alternative medicine in the hope of finding a solution to the problem. Bill Oddie goes in search of wildlife with a trip into the jungle, and opens up about how spending time in nature has helped him cope with mental-health issues.(n)

programme.title: Breakfast
programme.desc: A round-up of national and international news, plus sports reports, weather forecasts and arts and entertainment features. Including NewsWatch at 7.45.(n)

programme.title: Saturday Kitchen Live
programme.desc: Angela Hartnett serves as the host, as explorer Levison Wood joins her the studio, while chefs Carl Clarke and Niklas Ekstedt take up residence in the kitchen.(n)

programme.title: The Little Paris Kitchen: Cooking with Rachel Khoo
programme.desc: The pastry chef continues to display her passion and flair for the cuisine of Paris as she tries to prove that simple cooking can produce sensational results. In this episode, she enlists the expertise of a local baker to help her prepare baguettes, puts her own twist on a traditional boeuf Bourguignon, and creates a chocolate sponge oozing with salted caramel.(n)

programme.title: Football Focus
programme.desc: Dan Walker and guests look ahead to forthcoming fixtures, including Chelsea v Swansea City in the Premier League and Manchester United v Southampton in the EFL Cup final.(n)

programme.title: Bargain Hunt
programme.desc: Tim Wonnacott joins experts Anita Manning and Christina Trevanion at the Ardingly antiques fair in West Sussex, as they take two teams of contestants under their wings to search for collectibles. The presenter encounters an unusual find on his travels and some surprises unfold in the salesroom.(n)

programme.title: Live Six Nations Rugby Union
programme.desc: Scotland v Wales (Kick-off 2.25pm). John Inverdale presents coverage of the third match of this year's tournament for both sides, which takes place at Murrayfield. Vern Cotter's Scots will be hoping to end their dismal run of nine straight losses at the hands of the Welsh. After suffering a record 51-3 drubbing in Cardiff three years ago, Scotland have lost their last two meetings with Wales by the much smaller margins of three and four points respectively. Both teams narrowly lost a fortnight ago to France and England respectively and defeat here would almost certainly end any lingering title hopes. With commentary by Eddie Butler, Martyn Williams and Chris Paterson.(n)

programme.title: Final Score
programme.desc: Jason Mohammad presents a round-up of the classified results and this afternoon's news from the Premier League, EFL and Scotland.(n)

programme.title: Celebrity Mastermind
programme.desc: Fashion and beauty vlogger Louise Pentland, writer and comedian Jason Cook, Escape to the Country host Alistair Appleton and CBBC presenter Ben Shires demonstrate their knowledge of their chosen subjects, which are the Harry Potter novels, Billy Connolly, 20th-century European classical music and Leeds United. John Humphrys asks the questions.(n)

programme.title: Pointless Celebrities
programme.desc: Alexander Armstrong and Richard Osman present as more famous faces take part in the general knowledge quiz. This time, the celebrity teams come from the world of radio broadcasting, as Toby Anstis and Jenni Falconer, Janice Long and Bob Harris, Peter White and Steve Punt, and Angie Greaves and Steve Penk try to come up with the least likely correct answers to a series of questions posed to members of the public.(n)

programme.title: Let It Shine
programme.desc: The battle of the boy bands is almost over as the three finalists perform the two songs they hope will win them the starring roles in Gary Barlow's new musical based on the music of Take That. Adding to the excitement, Robbie Williams joins Dannii Minogue, Martin Kemp and Gary on the judging panel - and also reunites with his old bandmates Gary, Mark Owen and Howard Donald for a special medley of Take That hits. They'll no doubt show the contestants how it's done as they aim to impress the viewing voters. But whose stars will shine? Graham Norton and Mel Giedroyc are the ones with the answer. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Casualty
programme.desc: Steph, the woman responsible for Grace's hospitalisation, is rushed into the ER after attempting suicide in prison. The staff face an upward struggle in finding out what pills she has taken, one which is made all the more difficult by the patient's refusal to speak - and the cold distain of both Connie and Jacob. However, when it becomes clear Connie visited Steph in prison not long before she tried to claim her own life, things become even more complicated. Meanwhile, Iain helps Gem to get a job in the hospital coffee shop, and when Grace's continued silence is ruled as being a psychological issue, Sam decides it may be time to take her home.(n)

programme.title: Taboo
programme.desc: The time of reckoning arrives for both James Delaney and his nemesis Sir Stuart Strange, as Delaney confronts the East India Company chairman with the cold, hard truth. All the while, Delaney conspires to escape his circumstances, but as the enmity of the Prince Regent turns to lethal fury, the Crown unleashes one final, destructive plan. Time is running out for all three major players, and old scores must be settled - with all tragic consequences borne. Historical drama, starring Tom Hardy, Jonathan Pryce and Mark Gatiss. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Match of the Day
programme.desc: Gary Lineker presents highlights of the latest Premier League matches, including Chelsea v Swansea City at Stamford Bridge, Hull City v Burnley at the KCOM Stadium and Everton v Sunderland at Goodison Park. Antonio Conte's Blues are looking more and more likely to be crowned champions as each week goes by, and they will have been hoping to continue that title challenge against Paul Clement's Swans, stuck in their own battle against relegation.(n)

programme.title: This Country
programme.desc: The mockumentary explores waning faith in police forces wanes around the country, offering another snapshot of attitudes nationwide via a `typical' Cotswolds village. This time, Kerry and Kurtan await the release of their uncle, Steve `Nugget' Nuggins, who they believe was wrongfully imprisoned for `having a laugh'.(n)

programme.title: The World's Most Photographed
programme.desc: An exploration of how photography has been used and manipulated to construct the public personae of 10 major figures from history, beginning with the king of rock 'n' roll Elvis Presley. At the peak of his career, the singer's image was more carefully packaged than any other star before him, but Alfred Wertheimer talks about the series of spontaneous, unposed pictures he took of him as an unknown singer in New York, and a number of other photographers, including James Reid and Lew Allen, tell their own remarkable stories.(n)

programme.title: Wanted Down Under Revisited
programme.desc: Nicki Chapman finds out if Sheffield man Greg Wallen ever convinced his wife Jenni and stepdaughter Evie to make the move to New Zealand after their trial week in Auckland in 2015.(n)

programme.title: The Farmers' Country Showdown
programme.desc: Dorset-based sheep farmers Jo and Dan from Beaminster, and Jon and Justine from Stalbridge, get ready to show off the best of their flock at the Melplash Agricultural Show.(n)

programme.title: Big Dreams Small Spaces
programme.desc: In Essex, Denise has never ventured beyond the decking area behind her house but harbours ideas of having an altogether `dream-like' garden, including building ruins of a mill to remind her of childhood. Her husband Dave isn't quite as enthusiastic, not least the amount of work involved, so Monty Don is called in to mediate. Meanwhile in Suffolk, father-and-daughter team Rob and Jo's ambitious plan to build a productive terraced allotment on a treacherously steep slope in the middle of a wooded wasteland leaves Monty lost for words.(n)

programme.title: Victoria Derbyshire
programme.desc: Daily news and current-affairs programme offering discussion of breaking stories, exclusive interviews and audience interaction via social media.(n)

programme.title: BBC Newsroom Live
programme.desc: A chance to stay up to date on the day's leading stories, with the latest breaking news as it happens.(n)

programme.title: Daily Politics
programme.desc: Parliamentary proceedings interspersed with discussions, interviews and filmed reports from around the country, presented by Andrew Neil.(n)

programme.title: Coast
programme.desc: The team is `all at sea', revisiting some of the surprising off-shore stories featured throughout the series.(n)

programme.title: Beat the Brain
programme.desc: Quiz in which contestants face puzzles, problems, posers and conundrums designed to test every part of their mental fitness against the show's resident genius - The Brain. For every correct answer they accumulate seconds in their `brain bank' and improve their chances of winning a jackpot of £3,000. Hosted by John Craven, with Josie Lawrence as The Brain.(n)

programme.title: Landward
programme.desc: Dougie Vipond reports on an amazing new discovery by fossil hunters, Sarah Mack inspects winter crops from the air and Euan McIlwraith examines land reform.(n)

programme.title: Mountain
programme.desc: Griff Rhys Jones walks among the highest peaks of Snowdonia and explores the legends of his forefathers. The actor and comedian encounters rare wild Welsh mountain ponies, learns how ash deposited by the bereaved is affecting the ecological balance of the area and meets climbers choosing to battle the extreme conditions despite the provision of a railway. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Africa
programme.desc: David Attenborough continues his exploration of the continent in east Africa, which is a haven for life and supports a higher density of large mammals than anywhere else on Earth. From dense forests to snow-capped peaks, steamy swamps to endless savannah, it's also a land of unpredictable extremes, where creatures must adapt to survive. In Tanzania, a tiny lizard risks its life to eat flies from the face of a sleepy lion. The nesting habits of the 4ft shoebill are also captured on camera - the giant bird has two chicks, but due to sibling rivalry only one will survive. On the plains of Amboseli, a baby elephant is near to death in the drought, so its mother leaves the herd to stay with her offspring until the bitter end.(n)

programme.title: A Place to Call Home
programme.desc: Anna presents Elizabeth with the manuscript of House of Lies. Sarah decides on the name of her new baby and the trap to ensnare Regina is finally set.(n)

programme.title: Antiques Road Trip
programme.desc: Antiques experts Charles Hanson and Margie Cooper are pitted against each other as they travel across the UK in search of bargains. Their last leg starts in the village of Stickney, Lincolnshire, and leads the duo to the final auction in Leicester.(n)

programme.title: Eggheads
programme.desc: Quiz hosted by Jeremy Vine, in which the winners of famous game shows work as a team to tackle a new set of challengers.(n)

programme.title: Great Continental Railway Journeys
programme.sub-title: Pisa to Lake Garda - Part One.
programme.desc: Part one of two. Michael Portillo takes a trip in a Maserati sports car, and discovers how the leaning tower of Pisa was rescued from near collapse.(n)

programme.title: Big Dreams Small Spaces
programme.desc: In Blackpool, accountant Alex dreams of turning her boring backyard into a magical enchanted forest, complete with fairy lights and luscious woodland plants. Monty Don suggests a big and daring idea, and to illustrate his point, sends Alex to visit the ancient trees of Holker Hall in Cumbria. In Bristol, Ross has taken on a very overgrown allotment and wants a space to relax in as much as a vegetable garden. Monty boosts Ross' gardening know-how to help build his dream outside space.(n)

programme.title: Mastermind
programme.desc: John Humphrys hosts as five more semi-finalists compete for a place in the final. The specialised subjects are TV detective series The Sweeney, pioneering nurse and heroine of the Crimean War Mary Seacole, explorer James Cook, Tranmere Rovers and the travel writings of Bill Bryson.(n)

programme.title: Only Connect
programme.desc: Victoria Coren Mitchell hosts as the Surrealists take on the Korfballers in this quarter-final match. They must use patience, lateral thinking and sheer inspiration to make connections between groups of four things that may appear at first not to be linked, with one set of clues consisting of Tuvala, Hijab, Defra and Nope.(n)

programme.title: The Secrets of Your Food
programme.desc: Michael Mosley and James Wong reveal the physics, chemistry and biology hidden inside various foods. In the opening episode they explore how this chemistry fuels and builds bodies, with Michael sampling most people's first meal - human breast milk, which contains important fats, carbohydrates, vitamins and minerals. Michael and James also unravel why sourdough bread is so beneficial, how the rice has become a comforting staple food, and why allowing mushrooms to `sunbathe' may help provide a welcome calcium boost.(n)

programme.title: QI
programme.desc: The second of two editions showcasing highlights from the `N' series of the comedy panel game, featuring quizmaster Sandi Toksvig, regular panellist Alan Davies and a host of guest participants. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Newsnight
programme.desc: Analysis of the day's events, presented by Kirsty Wark.(n)

programme.title: Back in Time for Dinner
programme.sub-title: Further Back in Time for Dinner: 1940s.
programme.desc: The Robshaws enter the 1940s and experience a decade dominated by war and entirely fuelled by rations, including powdered egg, nettles on toast and imitation brawn. They are even one family member down as Fred is evacuated to the countryside, but the war brings them together too as they share a Woolton pie in their very own Anderson shelter, the girls go dancing with Debbie and some GIs, and they all start to recognise how the family meal to bring them together in the good and bad times.(n)

programme.title: Terry Pratchett: Back in Black
programme.desc: A dramatised documentary telling the story of the life of Terry Pratchett, the fantasy author whose popular Discworld series made him a household name, selling more then 85 million copies worldwide. In 2015, following a prolonged and very public battle with Alzheimers, Terry died, leaving behind one last unfinished story - his own. Here, actor Paul Kaye steps into the celebrated writer's shoes, charting Terry's life from his troubled schooldays and his difficulties securing the respect of literary critics, through to his eventual success, and his gradual decline into ill health. The film makes use of Terry's own words, along with those of his friend and collaborator Neil Gaiman, contemporary Val McDermid, and long-serving assistant Rob Wilkins.(n)

programme.title: Big Jim McLain
programme.desc: A zealous US government agent investigating un-American activities romances a suspected spy in the hope she will lead him to the mastermind behind a communist espionage ring operating from Hawaii. Drama, starring John Wayne, Nancy Olson, James Arness and Alan Napier.(n)

programme.title: Birds of Paradise: The Ultimate Quest
programme.desc: Part one of two. Thirty years ago explorer Benedict Allen lived in Papua New Guinea with the Niowra, a remote people. Broadcast journalist Frank Gardner has always wished to see wild birds of paradise, so Benedict resolves to take him along. The duo set out through some of the most inhospitable terrain on the planet, negotiating swamps, mountains and crocodile-infested waters, heading into the cloud forest. Despite Frank requiring the use of a wheelchair following a shooting incident in 2004, Benedict determines to get him to their destination.(n)

programme.title: The Brit Who Tried to Kill Trump
programme.desc: Documentary telling the story of Michael Sandford, a 20-year-old man from Surrey with Asperger's Syndrome who tried to assassinate Donald Trump during a 2016 political rally. The film follows his family as they travel to the US for his sentencing, and uses eyewitness accounts and archive footage to piece together the sequence of events and investigate the reasons behind it.(n)

programme.title: Royal Recipes
programme.desc: Michael Buerk is joined by chef Paul Ainsworth to celebrate food served to royal children, including cottage pie, said to be a favourite of Prince William.(n)

programme.title: This Is BBC Two
programme.desc: Preview of upcoming programmes from BBC Two.(n)

programme.title: They Flew Alone
programme.desc: Fact-based drama telling the story of 1930s British aviation pioneer Amy Johnson, who made history with a series of record-breaking solo flights around the world, before going on to aid the RAF in the Second World War. However, her rise to public acclaim placed a strain on her marriage to a fellow pilot. Starring Anna Neagle and Robert Newton.(n)

programme.title: In Which We Serve
programme.desc: When a British destroyer is torpedoed during the Battle of Crete, surviving crew members are left clinging to the wreckage and recall their previous adventures at sea - and the reasons why they enlisted for service in the first place. Second World War drama, starring Noel Coward, who co-directed with David Lean, alongside John Mills, Bernard Miles, Celia Johnson and Richard Attenborough.(n)

programme.title: Britain's Secret Seas
programme.desc: Paul Rose, Tooni Mahto and Frank Pope assist with the excavation of a 17th-century ship discovered in the waters outside Poole Harbour, Dorset, which could be one of the most important finds in British maritime history. They also learn about the plight of spiny seahorses in Dorset's Studland Bay, explore marine life beneath Brighton Pier and examine the wreck of an experimental Second World War submarine. Last in the series.(n)

programme.title: Homes Under the Hammer
programme.desc: Lucy Alexander, Martin Roberts and Dion Dublin meet an engaged couple at their first home in Newcastle, a new dad who has just bought a flat in Leyton, London, and a former IT worker starting a property development career in Gainsborough, Lincolnshire.(n)

programme.title: Two Greedy Italians
programme.sub-title: Two Greedy Italians: Still Hungry: Calabria and Bambinone.
programme.desc: Antonio Carluccio and Gennaro Contaldo return to Italy, where they continue their culinary journey. They begin in the southern region of Calabria, where they reminisce about their favourite childhood meals. Antonio reveals the secret of his hot packed-lunches while Gennaro shares his memories of the ritual pig kill. Featuring recipes for orzotto - a pork and pearl barley risotto - fish stew, and rice cake flavoured with orange.(n)

programme.title: Waterloo
programme.desc: Napoleon returns from exile on Elba and regains control of the French army in a bid to reclaim his empire and depose the king. Meanwhile, the Duke of Wellington marshals the allied forces for the fateful battle to come and the day that will change the course of history. Drama, with Rod Steiger, Christopher Plummer, Orson Welles, Jack Hawkins, Dan O'Herlihy, Michael Wilding and Virginia McKenna.(n)

programme.title: Natural World
programme.desc: The lives of white gyrfalcons and a pack of Arctic wolves on the frozen landscape of Ellesmere Island, Canada. The birds feed their young with the flesh of hares, while the lupine pack awaits the arrival of new cubs. Narrated by Simon Poland.(n)

programme.title: Mastermind
programme.desc: John Humphrys hosts as five more semi-finalists compete for a place in the final. The specialised subjects are TV detective series The Sweeney, pioneering nurse and heroine of the Crimean War Mary Seacole, explorer James Cook, Tranmere Rovers and the travel writings of Bill Bryson.(n)

programme.title: University Challenge
programme.desc: The quarter-finals continue, with two teams of four students battling it out to make it to the next stage of the competition as they try to win two matches and progress to the semi-finals. Jeremy Paxman asks the questions.(n)

programme.title: Only Connect
programme.desc: Victoria Coren Mitchell hosts as the Surrealists take on the Korfballers in this quarter-final match. They must use patience, lateral thinking and sheer inspiration to make connections between groups of four things that may appear at first not to be linked, with one set of clues consisting of Tuvala, Hijab, Defra and Nope.(n)

programme.title: The House That £100K Built
programme.desc: Journalist and curator Kieran Long and architect Piers Taylor visit Co Antrim, Northern Ireland, to follow the progress of Alistair and Karen, who are hoping that building their dream home will be the key to a mortgage-free life. Kieran and Piers hunt out ingenious ways to improve the couple's design so that they can get the best possible house on their budget.(n)

programme.title: Flog It
programme.desc: Will Axon and Michael Baggot value items in Ashbourne, Derbyshire, including a pearlware cow and an Asprey and Co picnic set. Paul Martin visits the Peak District to experience the thrills of harness racing.(n)

programme.title: Grand Tours of the Scottish Islands
programme.sub-title: Bridging the Gap: Scarp, Great Bernera and Scalpay.
programme.desc: Paul Murton journeys around the coast of the Long Island of Harris and Lewis, beginning on Scarp, travelling north to Great Bernera, then south east to Scalpay. These islands may seem to exist in the shadow of their much larger neighbours, but Paul discovers they have a distinct identity all of their own, as he hears remarkable stories of crofter rebellions, rocket mail and a rich local culture.(n)

programme.title: Diana: Designing a Princess
programme.desc: BBC Art, Culture and Entertainment correspondent Brenda Emmanus marks the forthcoming 20th anniversary of the death of Diana, Princess of Wales, with a documentary exploring the stories behind some of her most exquisite dresses, brought together for a new exhibition at Kensington Palace in February. As a thoroughly modern royal, Diana had an acute sense of the importance of fashion in controlling her own image, as well as an understanding that clothing could be an art form. Brenda visits the Conservation Studio at Hampton Court Palace as the dresses for the exhibition are prepared for display, hears from historians and cultural commentators, and speaks to some of the designers who dressed Diana. Includes contributions by Elizabeth Emmanuel, Victor Edelstein and David Sassoon.(n)

programme.title: Dad's Army
programme.desc: An invasion alert throws Mainwaring's hopeless would-be heroes into a panic, leading half the platoon to unwittingly launch an attack on the other half - who are holed up in Godfrey's cottage. Comedy from 1969, starring Arthur Lowe and Arnold Ridley.(n)

programme.title: My Old Lady
programme.desc: Premiere. A penniless New Yorker hopes to turn his fortunes around by selling his dead father's flat in Paris, only to find an eccentric elderly Englishwoman is living there - and under French law, he cannot sell until after she dies. As he gets to know his unexpected tenant, he discovers a side to his father that he never know. Comedy drama based on director Israel Horovitz's stage play, starring Maggie Smith, Kevin Kline and Kristin Scott Thomas.(n)

programme.title: QI XL
programme.desc: Stephen Fry hosts an extended version of the quiz with a difference, with guests Matt Lucas, Lucy Porter and Ross Noble joining regular panellist Alan Davies, focusing on medical matters.(n)

programme.title: Albert Nobbs
programme.desc: A woman in 19th-century Ireland has lived in disguise as a man for 30 years, holding down a job as a butler at a Dublin hotel. She meets a married house painter whom she discovers is a fellow cross-dresser, and is inspired by her new friend's happy life to seek a wife of her own. Period drama, starring Glenn Close, Mia Wasikowska, Aaron Taylor-Johnson and Janet McTeer.(n)

programme.title: World News Today
programme.desc: The day's leading stories.(n)

programme.title: Top of the Pops: 1983
programme.desc: Simon Bates and Peter Powell present the pop chart programme from April 7, 1983, featuring Dexys Midnight Runners, Culture Club, Joboxers, Twisted Sister, Michael Jackson, Tracie, FR David, Nick Heyward, Big Country and David Bowie.(n)

programme.title: The Good Old Days
programme.desc: A 1978 edition of the old-time music hall programme, chaired by Leonard Sachs. Mike Reid, Wilma Reading, Denny Willis and Company, Sheila Mathews, Michael Darbyshire, Josephine Gordon, Frankie Ferrer and Albert Aldred entertain an audience from the stage of the Leeds City Varieties. First shown on 7 February 1978.(n)

programme.title: Sounds of the Seventies
programme.sub-title: Roxy Music, Queen and Elton John.
programme.desc: BBC archive recordings of classic hits by Roxy Music, Elton John and Queen.(n)

programme.title: Pop Go the Sixties
programme.desc: Procul Harum's 1967 Top of the Pops performance of A Whiter Shade of Pale.(n)

programme.title: Queen: From Rags to Rhapsody
programme.desc: Documentary recalling the rock band's early years, spent struggling gigging at pubs and colleges, and following their progress up to the moment they captured the UK's hearts and minds with what was to become one of the greatest songs of all time - Bohemian Rhapsody. The documentary features contributions by band members and outtakes from recording sessions.(n)

programme.title: Queen: The Legendary 1975 Concert
programme.desc: The rock band in performance at London's Hammersmith Odeon on Christmas Eve in 1975, featuring early singles including Liar, Keep Yourself Alive, Now I'm Here and Bohemian Rhapsody, as well as Brian May showcasing his guitar skills in Brighton Rock.(n)

programme.title: Guitar Heroes at the BBC
programme.sub-title: Even More Guitar Heroes at the BBC.
programme.desc: Archive performances of the most iconic artists and bands from the 1960s and 1970s, featuring Pictures of Matchstick Men by Status Quo, the Who's single Long Live Rock, Tunnel of Love by Dire Straits and Lynyrd Skynyrd's classic Sweet Home Alabama. Plus, rare clips of George Benson, Leo Kottke, Link Wray and Tom Petty.(n)

programme.title: When Albums Ruled the World
programme.desc: Documentary exploring the heyday of LPs from the mid-1960s to the late 1970s, as bands and singers embraced the creative opportunities they offered for music and artwork. The programme also examines how the arrival of new formats heralded the end of the album's golden era. With contributions from Queen's Roger Taylor, Noel Gallagher, Mike Oldfield, the Doors' Ray Manzarek, Slash and Grace Slick of Jefferson Airplane.(n)

programme.title: Top of the Pops: 1983

programme.desc: A mechanic who moonlights as an underground race-car driver strives to take the top prize in America's most prominent street race in order to have his revenge against the ambitious ex-NASCAR champ who had him framed and sent to prison. Inspired by the popular video-game franchise of the same name, Need for Speed tells the story of garage owner Tobey Marshall (Aaron Paul). Desperate to keep his family-owned business afloat, Marshall forms an uncomfortable partnership with wealthy ex-NASCAR star Dino Brewster (Dominic Cooper). That partnership falls apart when a lucrative sale to car broker Julia Bonet (Imogen Poots) fails to pan out, and unscrupulous Brewster uses a tragic street-racing mishap to have the innocent Marshall incarcerated. Released from prison two years later, the vengeful Marshall plots to prove his mettle by winning the De Leon -- an illicit race showcasing the country's top underground talents. But getting to the De Leon will be no simple task, because not only has the ruthless Brewster put a bounty on Marshall's prized car, but the police are hot on his trail during the white-knuckle, coast-to-coast dash. Fortunately for Marshall, his loyal crew and Bonet are willing to help him get to the starting line in time for the big race. Scott "Kid Cudi" Mescudi, Ramon Rodriguez, and Michael Keaton co-star(n)

A strange videotape begins making the rounds in a town in the Pacific Northwest; it is full of bizarre and haunting images, and after watching it, many viewers receive a telephone call in which they are warned they will die in seven days. programme.desc: A handful of state troopers are put in the uncomfortable position of having to actually enforce the law in this high-spirited comedy. Mac (Steve Lemme), Thorny (Jay Chandrasekhar), Foster (Paul Stoter), and Rabbit (Erik Stolhanske) are four Vermont state troopers whose dedication to duty is not exactly an inspiration to law enforcement officers everywhere. Stationed in a small town near the Canadian border, the troopers don't have much to do, so they while away their hours smoking dope and harassing hapless motorists. Their superior officer, Capt. O'Hagan (Brian Cox), likes the boys and they try to keep their more outrageous antics out of his earshot, but they often run afoul of fellow trooper Farva (Kevin Heffernan), who insists on doing things by the book. When Governor Jessman (Lynda Carter) announces massive budget cuts for Vermont law enforcement personnel, things look bad for the troopers and they must quickly prove their worth or they'll be forced to look for real jobs. Appropriately enough, the troopers stumble upon some information regarding a group of marijuana dealers operating along the border; the guys figure this is just the sort of high-profile bust that could save their careers, but the police department of a nearby town gets wind of the troopers' plans. The Earlville police are no friends of the troopers, and they set out to ruin their moment of glory. Super Troopers was written by the five-man comedy troupe Broken Lizard, who also star as the five troopers; the group's leader, Jay Chandrasekhar, directed(n)

programme.title: Reign Of Fire
programme.desc: Medieval fantasy meets futuristic science fiction in this effects-heavy action epic from former X-Files director Rob Bowman. In present-day London, 12-year-old Quinn Abercromby witnesses the awakening of a hibernating dragon from a centuries-long slumber, the result of a construction dig supervised by his mother and an incident for which Quinn feels partially responsible. Twenty years later, the adult Quinn is the fire chief of a refortified castle community, responsible for dousing the blazes lit by the dragon's prodigious number of flame-spewing offspring, airborne juggernauts that have wreaked havoc across the globe, torching civilization and turning humans into an endangered species. Hope arrives in the form of Denton "Dragon Slayer" Van Zan, an American known to be the only man to ever kill one of the dragons, and Alex Jenson, a scientist/pilot who's a member of Van Zan's army, a zealous fighting force that includes a secret weapon: the Archangels, paratroopers using themselves as bait to attract and then dispatch the deadly beasts(n)

programme.title: The Mentalist
programme.desc: Jane suspects a blogger's fascination with serial killers may have led him to commit murder in an attempt to achieve a twisted kind of fame. Unfortunately the FBI takes over the case before he can gather enough evidence to make an arrest, prompting him to try another strategy. Aware that the suspect craves publicity, he arranges for him to appear on a TV talk show. Directed by and starring Simon Baker.(n)

programme.title: The Mentalist
programme.desc: Jane is called to a nightclub car park where an undercover policewoman has been shot, and discovers she was trying to obtain incriminating evidence against a drug kingpin - whose henchmen later kidnap him. His only chance of escape lies in playing a psychological game with the dead woman's partner, who appears to have begun to identify with her underworld contacts so closely that she has changed sides and become a criminal.(n)

programme.title: Law & Order: Criminal Intent
programme.desc: The chief financial officer of a hedge fund is killed at a banquet where it is rumoured the company is about to be investigated for fraud. The CEO soon checks himself into a psychiatric treatment facility, where patients include one of his major investors, prompting Wheeler and Nichols to investigate the activities of the men's psychiatrist.(n)

programme.title: Law & Order: Criminal Intent
programme.desc: An American football team's doctor is murdered in his home while his wife is tied up in their bedroom, after arguing with a player who blamed him for a drug scandal. Goren and Eames investigate the couple's preacher, who teaches an extremely tolerant and forgiving approach to adultery, and a member of the church's congregation who evades their questioning. Crime drama, starring Vincent D'Onofrio and Kathryn Erbe.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: Sarah Porter, the Secretary of the Navy, learns her daughter has been kidnapped, and the NCIS crew teams up with the FBI to track the case, determine a motive and bring her the abducted girl home. Meanwhile, McGee's childhood friend, NCIS Special Agent Valerie Page, arrives in town to assist with advanced tactics training. Naval crime drama, guest starring Leslie Hope and Christina Chang.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: The team looks into a raid on a naval base, and Dr Cyril Taft - the surgeon who saved Gibbs' life - experiences the thrill of assisting on an investigation. Assigned to treat Gibbs' suspect, Taft manages to uncover evidence that may prove crucial to solving the case. Meanwhile, DiNozzo pays his old flame Jeanne Benoit a visit as he chases a lead involving doctors in Sudan. Guest starring John Cryer and Scottie Thompson.(n)

programme.title: The Mentalist
programme.desc: A former American football star's assistant dies in a car bomb, which Jane believes was intended for the sportsman, so he sets up a ruse to make the killer believe the attack was successful and the athlete is dead. The team compiles a list of suspects and tries to draw out the criminal at a memorial service, but the investigators uncover a long list of enemies with different motives. Crime drama, starring Simon Baker and Robin Tunney.(n)

programme.title: The Mentalist
programme.desc: Jane is called to the scene of a fireman's death, but is knocked unconscious while searching for the murder weapon and almost drowns in a pond, which causes him to lose his memory and revert to his former con-artist self. Rigsby takes him under his wing, convinced the only way to get him firing on all cylinders again is to bring him back into the CBI fold. Crime drama, starring Simon Baker and Owain Yeoman.(n)

programme.title: Law & Order: Criminal Intent
programme.desc: A man involved in a bank heist is killed six months later in a deliberate explosion, and Nichols and Wheeler discover that one of his partners faked his own death. The detectives conclude that one of the robbers has decided not to split the money three ways, and may kill again to further increase their share. Crime drama, starring Jeff Goldblum and Julianne Nicholson.(n)

programme.title: Law & Order: Criminal Intent
programme.desc: Goren and Eames investigate when a hotel is targeted by robbers and a baby is kidnapped from one of the rooms while her parents are eating in the restaurant downstairs. Fragments of glass discovered at the scene give the detectives a lead, but it is not long before a ransom demand is made. Guest starring Piper Perabo and Luke Kirby.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: A day spent working on a cut-and-dried case leaves the team free to spend some time away from work, and while McGee and Delilah argue over the importance of keeping shop-talk to a minimum, DiNozzo ends up boring his dinner date with crime-solving tales. However, the agents' personal plans are all interrupted as, one-by-one, they realise errors have been made in closing their latest investigation. Starring Mark Harmon, David McCallum and Pauley Perrette.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: An American couple are attacked in Iraq, in the very same spot a group of US Special Ops snipers were ambushed six months earlier. Determined to get to the bottom of the case, Gibbs is forced to speak to Aaron Davis, the only survivor of the first assault, who is now struggling through PTSD at the Walter Reed Medical Center. The 300th episode of the military crime drama, starring Mark Harmon, David McCallum and Pauley Perrette.(n)

programme.title: NCIS
programme.desc: Ellie is sent to Gitmo to gather evidence in the case relating to the murder of a US Navy chaplain, and while there, she is given cause to question her previous work at the NSA.(n)

programme.title: To the Manor Born

programme.title: To the Manor Born

programme.title: Last of the Summer Wine

programme.title: Last of the Summer Wine

programme.sub-title: Ballad for Wind Instruments and Canoe.

programme.title: The Vicar of Dibley
programme.desc: First episode of Richard Curtis's comedy, starring Dawn French as the new vicar of a sleepy English village. Her arrival causes consternation among the locals - particularly stuffy councillor David Horton, who vows to have her ejected at all costs. Gary Waldhorn, James Fleet and Emma Chambers co-star.(n)

programme.title: The Vicar of Dibley
programme.desc: Part two of two. After a whirlwind romance with handsome newcomer Harry, Geraldine swaps her dog collar and cassock for a wedding dress, and hurriedly makes preparations for the big day. But the vicar she has chosen for the service seems a little too fond of her, while the villagers have waited until the last minute to suggest their ideas. The first is a skydiving wedding - the second is something far, far worse. Keeley Hawes and Hugh Bonneville guest star in the last-ever episode of the comedy, alongside Dawn French, Emma Chambers, Roger Lloyd Pack, James Fleet, Gary Waldhorn, Trevor Peacock and John Bluthal.(n)

programme.title: Only Fools and Horses
programme.desc: Always one to jump on the latest passing bandwagon, Del-Boy goes eco-friendly and decides to create a better world for baby Damien and his generation - by starting his own bottled water business. Starring David Jason, Nicholas Lyndhurst, Buster Merryfield and Tessa Peake-Jones. Christmas special from 1992.(n)

programme.title: Only Fools and Horses
programme.desc: A nagging toothache forces a reluctant Del to visit the dentist, but he gets more than he bargained for when the receptionist falls for him and embarks on a Fatal Attraction-style campaign to get her hooks into him. Meanwhile, Cassandra's plan to have a baby takes its toll on Rodney, who has never been so exhausted in all his life. Christmas special from 1993.(n)

programme.title: Only Fools and Horses
programme.desc: Del feels down on his luck after the council rejects his application for a home improvement grant, but his spirits are raised when he hears about a fancy-dress party across town. David Jason, Nicholas Lyndhurst and Buster Merryfield star as the wheeler-dealers in the first part of the Christmas 1996 trilogy. With Tessa Peake-Jones, Gwyneth Strong, Douglas Hodge and Angela Bruce.(n)

programme.title: Only Fools and Horses
programme.desc: Del buys a new manual to help him show Raquel more appreciation and give him the confidence to make positive decisions. Unfortunately, as a result of such upbeat thinking, the Trotters' cash flow hits an all-time low and an angry punter is left baying for blood. The second part of the Christmas 1996 trilogy, starring David Jason, Tessa Peake-Jones and Nicholas Lyndhurst.(n)

programme.title: Blackadder
programme.desc: It is 1485 and Edmund, Duke of Edinburgh's accidental killing of his great-uncle Richard III at the Battle of Bosworth Field leads to his father becoming king. However, he also manages to help his parent's arch-enemy to escape - and meets faithful sidekick Baldrick for the first time. First episode of the comedy, guest starring Peter Cook, with Rowan Atkinson and Brian Blessed.(n)

programme.title: Blackadder
programme.sub-title: Blackadder Goes Forth: Plan F - Goodbyeee.
programme.desc: Capt Blackadder tries every trick in the book to escape the trenches before the big push, including pretending to be insane - but ends up going over the top with sidekicks Baldrick and George. Final episode of the comedy, guest starring Geoffrey Palmer, with Rowan Atkinson, Tony Robinson and Hugh Laurie.(n)

programme.title: Not Going Out
programme.desc: First episode of the sitcom about a drifter whose friendship with his flatmate is complicated by the fact her ex-boyfriend is his best mate. programme.title: Not Going Out
programme.desc: Tim and Kate's closeness following the death of his grandmother becomes a cause for concern for Lee, so he shares his worries with a counsellor - who is unimpressed by his lack of social skills. programme.title: Not Going Out
programme.desc: Lee clashes with a youth when he gets a job distributing leaflets in a shopping centre, and is persuaded to pretend to be Tim in front of Kate's Australian friend Ruth, who has landed on their doorstep. Comedy, starring Lee Mack, Tim Vine and Megan Dodds.(n)

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: Sue Perkins and Mel Giedroyc present as the remaining four bakers take a deep breath and head into the semi-final of the nation's favourite baking contest. However, there's no time to marvel at how far they've come - it's Patisserie Week, and they will need to demonstrate that they have skills worthy enough to see them through to this year's final. The bakers are challenged to make a signature baklava - two types of any flavour they like, before the technical challenge demands they knock up a German Schichttorte, a cake cooked in stages under the grill to create 20 layers of different coloured sponge. Finally, the showstopper sees the semi-finalists baking non-stop to create two entremets in which they should demonstrate as many personal skills and techniques as they can.(n)

programme.title: MasterChef
programme.desc: The last quarter-final sees the four heat winners take on the fiendishly difficult palate test, recreating John Torode's Singapore chilli crab, having only had a couple of minutes to taste the dish and write down what they think the ingredients are. It's a tricky recipe with a fiery chilli and black-bean paste that also requires them to prepare and cook a whole crab. Can they rise to the challenge? They then rustle up a showstopping dish for the judges and food critic Kate Spicer, before finding out who has made it through to the semi-finals.(n)

programme.title: MasterChef
programme.desc: After five weeks of heats, 60 hopefuls have been whittled down to the most promising 10. But if they thought it was tough getting this far, the knockout stage will really sort the dishwashers from the chefs, as over the next two nights the remaining contestants are split into two groups of five and get their first taste of professional cooking. Tonight's group heads to London's Caxton Grill, where 2013 MasterChef: The Professionals finalist Adam Handling is head chef for a busy lunchtime service. Then it's back to the studio to rustle up a dish from an array of seasonal produce for renowned chef Marcus Wareing and the judges, John Torode and Gregg Wallace, who will then send one of the hopefuls home.(n)

programme.desc: Australian director Jamie Blanks helmed this teen horror film set at Pendleton University. Campus legend has it that 25 years earlier Pendleton was the site of a mass murder by a demented abnormal psych instructor who killed six students and then himself. However, no proof of the prof's deed remains. Urban legends are the subject of a course in American folklore taught by Professor Wexler (Robert Englund). When a series of bizarre deaths occur on the campus, assertive student Natalie thinks they are murders based on urban legends, but classmates Brenda (Rebecca Gayheart), ambitious journalism major Paul (Jared Leto), and practical joker Damon (Joshua Jackson) claim it's just a coincidence. Then Natalie begins to realize that she's the next victim. programme.title: Brown Sugar
programme.desc: A woman wonders if it's just friendship or real love she feels when a close male friend announces he's tying the knot in this romantic comedy. Dre (Taye Diggs) and Sidney (Sanaa Lathan) became best friends when they were ten years old -- the same time that both first became aware of the first rumblings of the Hip Hop revolution in New York City. Today, Dre runs a successful record label, and Sidney is a respected music journalist; both have managed to turn their love for the music into careers, and both are still close friends. Close enough, in fact, that many of their pals wonder why they've never become boyfriend and girlfriend. While both have always denied their attraction to one another, Sidney begins to have second thoughts when Dre proposes to his girlfriend Reese (Nicole Ari Parker), a lawyer. Even though Sidney has a relationship of her own with professional basketball player Kelby (Boris Kodjoe), as Dre's wedding draws closer, Sidney begins to suspect that her longtime best friend is actually the love of her life. Brown Sugar features supporting performances form real life Hip Hop stars Mos Def and Queen Latifah; former basketball star Earvin "Magic" Johnson served as executive producer(n)

programme.desc: Director Brian Robbins' sci-fi comedy stars Eddie Murphy as both a man-sized humanoid spaceship and the diminutive captain of the same vessel. programme.title: Junior
programme.desc: Ultimate manly man Arnold Schwarzenegger learns what it's like to be an expectant mother in director Ivan Reitman's high-concept comedy. Schwarzenegger plays Dr. Hess, a medical researcher working on a revolutionary drug to help mothers carry endangered infants to term. When government regulations prevent Dr. Hess from testing the drug through normal channels, his partner Dr. Arbogast (Danny DeVito) develops an unorthodox solution: they will steal a female egg and implant it in Hess, who will carry the child himself. Predictably, much of the subsequent humor centers on the incongruous sight of the muscular Schwarzenegger undergoing the trials and tribulations of pregnancy, from morning sickness to labor pains. Emma Thompson returns to her comic roots and provides romantic interest as an incorrigibly clumsy but intelligent scientist who catches on to Hess' deception. Reitman, Schwarzenegger, and DeVito had previously had a hit with Twins (1988), which revolved around a similarly ludicrous medical premise, but they failed to repeat that film's success here, as audiences largely ignored the film and reviewers criticized the humor as disappointingly obvious(n)

programme.sub-title: Standish, Gloucestershire: Going Upmarket with the Romans.
programme.desc: Tony Robinson and the crew scour a field near Standish in Gloucestershire for signs of a Roman villa. While plenty of evidence of the building has been found, there is no trace of the structure itself. As the archaeologists search the area, they uncover signs of habitation from the Iron Age to the Roman era and discover the story of a family that lived through a tumultuous period of social change.(n)

programme.title: Time Team
programme.desc: Tony Robinson and the team explore Wemyss Caves in Fife, a landmark thought to have been inhabited by the Picts - a people so fearsome the Romans built Hadrian's Wall to keep them at bay. The experts examine the caverns, which are gradually eroding, hoping to find evidence of the native inhabitants, as well as the possibility of later occupants such as medieval Christian hermits and Jacobean nobles.(n)

programme.title: Great Canal Journeys
programme.desc: Timothy West and Prunella Scales travel from Birmingham to Braunston, Northamptonshire, to attend a festival of vintage canal boats, aided on the tricky journey by their son Sam and Juliet, Timothy's daughter from his first marriage. programme.title: Car SOS
programme.desc: Tim Shaw and Fuzz Townshend head to Eastbourne on the south coast to restore a 1962 Mini Cooper. programme.title: Secret History
programme.sub-title: The Dambusters' Great Escape: Secret History.
programme.desc: Dubbed `The Beast' by Winston Churchill, Tirpitz was Nazi Germany's most powerful battleship. Protected by an elite squadron of fighters, it was seen as invincible, but after 34 failed attempts to sink it, the RAF sent in the 617 `Dambusters' Squadron and 9 Squadron. In a raid in November 1944 they managed to slip through enemy defences and destroy Tirpitz. With eyewitness accounts from surviving RAF crew, one of the Luftwaffe fighter pilots and German sailors, this documentary tells this extraordinary story and offers new evidence to explain the mission's improbable success.(n)

programme.title: Fatal Flight 447: Chaos in the Cockpit
programme.desc: The story of what really happened on June 1, 2009, when Air France Flight 447 from Rio de Janeiro to Paris plummeted into the Atlantic Ocean, killing all 228 passengers and crew. It remained a mystery how one of the world's most technologically advanced planes could seemingly just drop out of the sky, until a two-year search finally located the black-box recorders. This documentary reveals the scene on board the doomed airliner as the pilots struggled to understand the catastrophe unfolding before them, and asks what lessons have been learnt from the disaster.(n)

programme.title: The Plane Crash
programme.desc: Scientists, pilots and aviation experts participate in a staged aeroplane crash in a remote area of Mexican desert, hoping the exercise will reveal more about what happens to aircraft and their occupants during forced emergency landings. Pilot James `JimBob' Slocum will put a Boeing 727 passenger jet on a crash course, parachuting out minutes before impact - with former US Navy pilot Leland `Chip' Shanle then taking charge of the craft via remote control from a chase plane. After the crash, experts will analyse the site, along with data collected from cameras, instruments and hi-tech crash test dummies, to learn more about what happens when planes are forced out of the sky.(n)

programme.title: Naked Science
programme.desc: Birth of Oceans. 70% of Earth's surface is covered with liquid water but how did it get here? Our water is one of the greatest paradoxes in science today, because although cool enough to have water now, things where much hotter when our planet first formed. At 93 million miles from the sun it was too hot for Earth to form with water, so where did our oceans come from? For decades scientists were in agreement that it was delivered from the cold outer reaches of the solar system by icy comets. However, in the 1980s the discovery that comet water was subtly different to the water on Earth left scientists baffled, they had to put aside everything they thought they knew and start again. This puzzle has lead to a number of different theories, however most now think that Earth's water arrived in a number of different ways and this has amazing implications. If Earth has more than one source of water then the chances of finding another Earth-like planet that also has liquid water have just shot up, and because you can't have life without this magic liquid, so too have the chances that we are not alone(n)

Comedy, starring Dakota Johnson, Rebel Wilson, Alison Brie and Leslie Mann.(n)

programme.desc: Homer unwittingly pollutes Lake Springfield, so the US government decides to isolate the city underneath a giant dome. The Simpsons manage to escape and plan to start a new life in Alaska - but learn Springfield is about to be destroyed, and return to save their friends. With the voices of Dan Castellaneta, Julie Kavner, Nancy Cartwright and Yeardley Smith.(n)

He is determined that his own road trip with his wife and kids will go better - but soon finds the apple has not fallen far from the tree. Sequel to the 1980s comedy series, starring Ed Helms and Christina Applegate, with Chevy Chase and Beverly D'Angelo reprising their roles.(n)

programme.desc: A boy ridiculed for his size makes a wish on a fairground machine to become bigger - only to wake up as a 30-year-old man. Driven from his home by his terrified mother, the bewildered youngster trapped in a grown-up body makes his way to New York, where he rises high in the ranks of a toy manufacturing company and applies his youthful enthusiasm to the complexities of adult life. Comedy, starring Tom Hanks, Elizabeth Perkins and Robert Loggia.(n)

He embarks on a campaign of publicity stunts to make himself famous, encountering prejudice and meeting people similarly desperate for stardom. Spoof documentary, starring Sacha Baron Cohen and Gustaf Hammarsten.(n)

programme.desc: Nightclub singer Deloris Van Cartier agrees to testify against her gangster boyfriend after witnessing a murder. Placed in protective custody by the authorities, she is less than pleased to discover she is expected to pose as chaste nun Sister Mary Clarence in a convent. Comedy, starring Whoopi Goldberg, Harvey Keitel, Maggie Smith, Bill Nunn and Kathy Najimy.(n)

programme.desc: A jaded computer programmer goes to bizarre lengths to get fired from his dull job - but his new laid-back attitude leads to unexpected promotions as his arrogance is taken for supreme self-confidence by unwitting bosses. Satirical comedy, starring Ron Livingston, Jennifer Aniston, Ajay Naidu and Gary Cole.(n)

programme.title: The Curse of the Pink Panther
programme.desc: Inspector Clouseau vanishes without trace and another detective must be chosen to solve the mystery of his disappearance. Glad to be rid of the bane of his existence, Clouseau's long-suffering boss makes sure an even more inept investigator gets the job. Comedy, starring Herbert Lom, Ted Wass, Joanna Lumley, David Niven and Robert Wagner.(n)

programme.title: Valentine's Day
programme.desc: Anthology of stories charting the romantic complications of various Los Angeles residents. A businessman and a soldier on leave share a flight home, a teacher is smitten with a doctor and an elderly couple comfort their lovesick grandson. Romantic comedy drama, with Ashton Kutcher, Jessica Alba, Jamie Foxx, Jennifer Garner and Julia Roberts.(n)

programme.title: Norbit
programme.desc: A timid man's life is ruined after he is bullied into marrying an overbearing, overweight woman. However, a more hopeful future beckons when he bumps into his childhood sweetheart and realises she is his one true love - but first he has to pluck up the courage to confront his tyrannical wife. Comedy, starring Eddie Murphy in multiple roles alongside Thandie Newton, Cuba Gooding Jr and Terry Crews.(n)

programme.title: Two Night Stand
programme.desc: A woman recovering from a recent break-up has a one-night stand with a stranger she met online. Hoping to leave quietly in the morning, she instead discovers a blizzard has left them both trapped in his apartment, forcing them to spend an awkward but enlightening day together. Romantic comedy, starring Analeigh Tipton and Miles Teller.(n)

They return to the family home to clear out their childhood bedrooms, but with their parents away, seize the chance to relive their teenage years and throw one last wild house party. Comedy, starring Amy Poehler, Tina Fey and Dianne Wiest.(n)

Comedy, starring Will Ferrell and Mark Wahlberg.(n)

programme.desc: A woman with dreams of becoming a journalist takes a job as assistant to the editor of a prestigious fashion magazine - a position that should guarantee a bright future if she succeeds. Unfortunately, she has just signed up to work for the boss from hell, whose cruel personality and outrageous demands make her life a nightmare. Comedy drama, with Meryl Streep, Anne Hathaway, Stanley Tucci and Emily Blunt.(n)

programme.desc: Frustrated heavy metal band the Lone Rangers are determined to get air time for their new record and take a radio station hostage to ensure it happens. Comedy, starring Steve Buscemi, Brendan Fraser, Adam Sandler and Michael McKean.(n)

Comedy from the Farrelly brothers, starring Cameron Diaz, Ben Stiller, Matt Dillon and Lee Evans.(n)

programme.desc: A baby princess's hair has mystical powers, so an evil witch kidnaps her and locks her in a tower, hoping to use the magic to fend off old age. When the princess is a teenager with 70-foot long tresses, she escapes with the aid of a bandit and goes in search of her home, but the witch is not going to let her go without a fight. Disney animated comedy based on the Rapunzel story, with the voices of Mandy Moore and Zachary Levi.(n)

Animated adventure, with the voices of John Travolta and Miley Cyrus.(n)

When the disappearance of an otter hints at a terrible conspiracy in the city, she enlists the aid of a con-artist fox in solving the mystery. Disney animated comedy, with the voices of Ginnifer Goodwin, Jason Bateman and Idris Elba.(n)

Disney animated musical, featuring the voices of Matthew Broderick, Jeremy Irons, Rowan Atkinson, Whoopi Goldberg and James Earl Jones.(n)

Romantic fantasy, starring Lily James, Cate Blanchett, Richard Madden and Helena Bonham Carter.(n)

programme.desc: A spoilt and uncaring emperor learns the importance of treating people fairly when a sorceress turns him into a llama so she can seize power herself.
